cs.DC, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.NE, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with a fundamental problem in distributed computing. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the distribution of requests to servers, which involves information transmission and processing. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper studies a system of servers processing incoming requests and analyzes its stability. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is less likely but still possible as the paper proposes a new variant of the balls into bins process and studies its performance, which can be seen as an optimization problem. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is also less likely but relevant as the paper analyzes the system load and proposes a distribution scheme to minimize it.
